MANUFACTURERS HANOVER Corp., New York, offered 12 million common shares at $43.50 a share as part of a major recapitalization announced recently by the bank holding company.
A syndicate led by Morgan Stanley & Co. is offering 10 million of the shares in the U.S.; the rest are being offered abroad.
U.S. underwriters have an option to buy as many as 1.8 million additional shares at the same price to cover overallotments.
Manufacturers currently has about 51 million shares outstanding. 

